    "In 2023, 70 papers (18.18%) were published, but the most striking surge occurred in 2024, which accounts for 199 papers-over half (51.69%) of the total sample.",
    "This substantial rise underscores a growing academic and policy interest in leveraging AI for climate resilience.",
